  "doc_id": "7768",
  "text": "Death resulting from traumatic injury occurs in a trimodal distribution. The first mode is death that directly results from the severity of the injury; this is typically associated with death at the scene of the injury. The second mode is early death because of hypoxia, hypovolemia, or head injury. The third type of mortality occurs in the days and weeks following injury and accounts for up to 45% of trauma-related deaths. [CITATION_1] Patients in this category typically die in the hospital as a result of head injury, acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS), or multiple organ failure syndrome (MOFS).",
