      "span_text": "The third type of mortality occurs in the days and weeks following injury and accounts for up to 45% of trauma-related deaths.  Patients in this category typically die in the hospital as a result of head injury, acute respiratory distress syndrome (ARDS), or multiple organ failure syndrome (MOFS)."
